CLEAN ROOM — fellipebrito.com
==================================================================
Project : Reverse-engineer fellipebrito.com (Framer-hosted) →
          local wireframe-style scaffold editable via Claude Code.
Owner   : Fellipe Brito
Started : 2026-04-27
Driver  : NOVA (Engineer Augmented Framework)

PURPOSE OF THIS LOG
-------------------
Fellipe wants a full audit trail so he can later review:
  - which agents NOVA used and why
  - exact prompts sent to each agent
  - summaries of what each agent returned
  - architectural decisions and revisions
This log is the artifact, not the conversation.

PLAN
----
Phase 0 — Init: directory structure + log header
Phase 1 — Discovery: single agent extracts per-page dossier
          (content, structure, assets, meta) + sitemap
Phase 2 — Synthesis: wireframe agent produces markdown
          wireframes + component inventory + IA sitemap
Phase 3 — Scaffold: agent generates semantic HTML stubs with
          minimal outline CSS, browsable locally

ARCHITECTURE NOTE — Phase 1 collapse
------------------------------------
Original proposal (agreed by Fellipe): 4 parallel parser agents
(Crawler, Content, Structure, Asset). NOVA revised pre-launch to
1 unified Discovery agent. Reason: WebFetch returns processed
content, not raw HTML, so splitting "fetch" from "parse" multiplies
network calls without adding parallelism. One agent with structured
extraction prompts produces identical outputs with less context
churn. Logged here so the design choice is visible.

OUTPUT TREE
-----------
clean-room/
  pages/<slug>.md        — per-page dossier from Phase 1
  sitemap.json           — Phase 1 manifest
  wireframes/<slug>.md   — Phase 2 wireframes
  components.md          — Phase 2 reusable blocks
  sitemap.md             — Phase 2 IA tree
  scaffold/              — Phase 3 HTML stubs
    index.html
    <path>/index.html
    wireframe.css

