=== [2026-04-27] PHASE 1 — DISCOVERY — DONE ===

PROMPT SENT (verbatim) — see prompt block below.

----- PROMPT -----
You are the Discovery agent for a Clean Room reverse-engineering of
fellipebrito.com (a Framer-hosted personal site). NOVA is building a
local, editable wireframe replica.

Goal: per-page dossier for every public page + top-level sitemap.

Steps: (1) try /sitemap.xml, fall back to homepage BFS depth=1.
       (2) for each URL, WebFetch with structured prompt asking for
           title, meta, heading hierarchy, nav, sections (verbatim
           copy), CTAs, footer, forms, embeds.
       (3) write clean-room/pages/<slug>.md per page + sitemap.json.
       (4) report concise summary (under 300 words).

Constraints: WebFetch only; no asset downloads; verbatim copy in
sections; cap at 50 pages.

Slug rules: / -> index ; /a -> a ; /a/b -> a--b.
------------------

RESULT SUMMARY
--------------
- discovery method: sitemap.xml (clean, 30 URLs)
- pages dossiered : 30 of 30 attempted
- failures        : 1  (/404 returns HTTP 404 on direct access)
- output dir      : clean-room/pages/ (30 files)
- manifest        : clean-room/sitemap.json

KEY FINDINGS (Phase 2 must know)
--------------------------------
1. Site is the paid Framer template "Newsbook" by Moise David.
   Template chrome is leaking on 4 pages (privacy-policy, style-guide,
   licenses, passworld) — NOT Fellipe's content. NOVA decision: Phase 2
   will skip these unless Fellipe overrides.
2. Global chrome is identical sitewide. Nav: [Fellipe Brito | Home |
   Blog]. Footer: same. No About/Work/Contact routes exist.
3. Site is purely a blog. 1 home + 5 blog index/category routes (all,
   bible, music, tech, golf) + 20 articles = 26 content pages worth
   wireframing.
4. Every article ends with a STATIC "Recent Post" widget showing the
   same 3 cards (we-never-lose / ai-where-i-m-drawing-the-line /
   a-conversation-with-my-anxiety) — not dynamic related-posts.
5. Every page expected to render an H2 "Get Notifications For Each
   Fresh Post" newsletter block — Framer-native form, fields/action
   did not surface via WebFetch (JS-rendered). Phase 2 should reserve
   a wireframe slot but mark form internals as "TBD: needs browser
   inspection".
6. Category index pages (Golf, Tech especially) partially failed to
   surface card grids via WebFetch. Canonical list is /blog/all;
   /blog/{bible,music,tech,golf} are filtered views. Phase 2 should
   wireframe categories as variants of /blog/all.
7. Oldest article 2015, references dead code.fellipebrito.com
   subdomain (content was migrated). Newest is 2026-04-14 Masters piece.
8. Card-listing pages show placeholder date "July 25, 2023" on every
   card — Framer template default. Real dates live inside article
   pages.

NOVA DECISIONS BEFORE PHASE 2
-----------------------------
- Skip 4 template-leak pages from wireframing (flagged to Fellipe).
- Treat /blog/{bible,music,tech,golf} as variants of /blog/all.
- Mark newsletter form internals as TBD.
- Recent-posts widget = shared component, not per-article.

