=== [2026-04-27] PHASE 4 — RESEARCH — DONE ===
All 4 parallel agents completed.

R1 PATTERN SCAN     | 12 sites + 2 bonus | 01-pattern-scan.md (266 lines)
  Top 3 patterns   : 2-sentence hero / 3-noun tagline / newsletter w/ social proof
  Top 2 antipatterns: stale time-stamps in nav / mononym hero from non-famous
  Surprise         : Tim Challies's anti-AI footer line — 2026 differentiator

R2 IDENTITY LAYER   | 13 sites surveyed   | 02-identity-layering.md (186 lines)
  6 strategies     : Faith-Forward Hero, Layered Bridge, Credentialed Polymath,
                     Faith-Coded Nav, Tagged-Content Split, Two-Site Split
  Best examples    : John Dyer (j.hn) / Russell Moore
  Hard antipattern : Christianese / Latin / verses in hero
  Recommendation   : Compound conjunction hero (Dyer/Moore model)

R3 TRACK-RECORD     | 6 patterns + 2 layouts | 03-track-record.md (263 lines)
  Best mixed comp  : Josh Mateo (employer narrative + nested client roster)
  Logo verdict     : Use logos in 2 labeled tiers (recognizable / industry-specific)
  Layout pick A    : Mateo Hybrid (RECOMMENDED)
  Layout pick B    : Selected Work List (text-only fallback)
  Header verb      : "Selected Work" + "Where I've been embedded" / "Shipped for"

R4 FUNNEL UX        | 30+ sources         | 04-funnel-ux.md (272 lines)
  CTA verdict      : Asymmetric single-primary; newsletter dominant in hero
  Anti-pattern #1  : Two equal-weight CTAs in hero (decision paralysis)
  Newsletter       : Hero + footer + inline-mid-article; NO popups/sticky/exit-intent
  Form             : Embed on /work page, never link out to forms.gle
  Submit copy      : "Tell me about it" / "Send your project" — never "Submit"

CROSS-RESEARCH TENSIONS SURFACED FOR PHASE 5
--------------------------------------------
1. Newsletter-dominant CTA (R4 data) vs client-primary audience (Fellipe's stated
   priority). Phase 5 surfaces both as options.
2. Google Form (Fellipe's pick) vs Tally/Typeform (R4's recommendation).
   Phase 5 surfaces tradeoff; deferrable.
3. 4-noun identity (Christian/Entrepreneur/Tech/Solutions) vs 3-noun research
   ceiling. Phase 5 proposes Tech+Solutions merge.

